Implementation details for ECR image push (P0.6):

WHY: Local images (e.g., 'myapp:latest') cannot be pulled by ECS Fargate from the local
Docker daemon. The deploy flow creates an ECR repo but never pushes images, causing
tasks to fail and ALB to return 503 errors.

WHAT WAS DONE:
1. isLocalImage(imageRef string) bool - Classifies image references:
   - ECR URIs (*.dkr.ecr.*.amazonaws.com/*) -> use as-is
   - Public registries (docker.io, ghcr.io, etc.) -> use as-is
   - Local images (name:tag without registry) -> push to ECR

2. pushImageToECR() implementation:
   - Gets ECR auth token via ecr:GetAuthorizationToken
   - Decodes base64 token to get username:password
   - Creates Docker client via docker/client SDK
   - Tags local image with ECR URI
   - Pushes image with registry auth
   - Reads push response stream for errors
   - Returns full ECR URI for task definition

3. Deploy flow updated:
   - After ensureECRRepository(), check isLocalImage()
   - If local, call pushImageToECR() to get ECR URI
   - Pass ECR URI (not original imageRef) to createTaskDefinition()

TESTING:
- Added TestIsLocalImage with 19 test cases covering all classification scenarios
- Mock implementation added for GetAuthorizationToken

